FISHING REPORT: WITH THIS TROUT, KEY IS QUALITY, NOT QUANTITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For Bill Maynor, the three-pound rainbow trout he caught Monday represents a 
catch of a lifetime. 
</P>
<P>
 Maynor, of Bakersfield, used Power Bait to take the fish on the last day of 
the Isabella Derby at Lake Isabella in Kern County. The fish didn't fight much, 
but it carried a tag worth $10,000. 
</P>
