ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; ACADEMY WILL OFFER OPEN HOUSE IN APRIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Hebrew Academy is having a series of open houses in April at which 
potential students and their families can learn about the school's educational 
offerings. 
</P>
<P>
 The academy, a kindergarten-through-12th-grade school affiliated with the 
Hasidic Lubavitch movement, is a private school with a full secular program as 
well as Jewish studies. About 400 students attend. 
</P>
<P>
 Open houses will be April 6 at 9 a.m., 10:30 a.m. and 2:30 p.m.; April 7 at 7 
p.m.; and April 12 at 7:30 p.m. The academy is at 14401 Willow Lane. For more 
information, call (714) 898-0051. JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
