ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; HOSPITAL SPONSORS HEALTH SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Second-year college students pursuing a career in the medical, dental or other 
health professions are eligible for scholarships offered by the Auxiliary of 
Volunteers of La Palma Intercommunity Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications will be considered based on an individual's chosen field and 
financial need. Students must have a grade-point average of at least 3.0 and 
must reside in La Palma, Cerritos, Cypress, Buena Park, Anaheim, Stanton, 
Lakewood or Hawaiian Gardens. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional scholarships are available to former or current VolunTEENS of La 
Palma Intercommunity Hospital who live in La Palma and will graduate from high 
school this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available in the lobby of La Palma Intercommunity Hospital, 
7901 Walker St. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 670-6024. 
</P>
