<HEADLINE>
<P>
OILERS' NOFFSINGER TOSSES PERFECT GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior Stefanie Noffsinger pitched a perfect game with 13 strikeouts as host 
Huntington Beach beat Rosary, 4-0, Tuesday in a Sunset League softball game. 
</P>
<P>
 It was Noffsinger's second no-hitter this season. She also has pitched two 
one-hitters for the Oliers (7-1, 2-0 in league). 
</P>
<P>
 Jessica Walker had two hits, including an RBI double, and scored a run for 
Huntington Beach. 
</P>
