<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP TENNIS ROUNDUP; THIRD-RANKED UNIVERSITY BEATS BAD VIBES, WOODBRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There's nothing like using the power of negative thinking to pull out a close 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 University High tennis Coach Josh Davis said he had some bad vibes going into 
Tuesday's match against archrival Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 "We did not practice well Monday," Davis said. "I knew this would be our 
toughest Sea View League match of the first round." 
</P>
<P>
 Trojan senior Seth Turbow felt even worse about playing Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm always a negative thinker," Turbow said. "I usually expect to lose. I 
knew they were good." 
</P>
<P>
 Fifth-ranked Woodbridge was good, but not quite good enough, losing to 
third-ranked University, 13 2/3-7 1/3, at Woodbridge's North Lake Tennis Club 
in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors led, 3 2/3-3 1/3, after the first round, but University (7-2, 
5-0) took nine of the last 12 sets to win going away. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our seniors pulled us through," Davis said. "Jason Meyers, Seth Turbow, 
Robbie Wilkins and Jason Maddox came through for us." 
</P>
<P>
 Meyers won all three of his singles sets, 6-0, 6-0, 6-4, and Maddox won, 6-2, 
4-6, 6-3. But Turbow and Wilkins, who played together at No. 1 doubles, won 
perhaps the two biggest sets of the day. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing Chris Coleman and Tom Ro, 5-4, Wilkins and Turbow came back to win 
the set, 7-6. Wilkins and Turbow won despite Turbow blowing three easy volleys 
in the tiebreaker. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just made sure I didn't do anything with my racket after I missed those 
shots," Turbow said. "My temper can be pretty bad." 
</P>
<P>
 Turbow and Wilkins settled down to win their next two sets, 6-0, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge fell to 8-3 and 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 "I expected it to be close, but it's kind of frustrating coming this close and 
not winning," Woodbridge Coach Joan Willett said. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have to give them credit. They came out really strong in the last round. 
I'm just glad we have another crack at them." 
</P>
<P>
 In another Sea View League match: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 20, Tustin 1 -- The doubles teams for Irvine (5-5, 1-4) swept their 
sets to give the Vaqueros their first league victory. Todd Herrington and 
Gonzalvo Funzalida won, 6-1, 6-3, 6-0. Anup Arora and Brad Thomas won, 6-2, 
6-0, 6-2, and Jeff Chen and Albert Tzeng won, 7-6, 6-3, 6-2. In singles, John 
Manley won his sets, 6-3, 6-1, 6-1, and Sid Khanijou won, 6-3, 6-2, 6-0. Tustin 
is 0-5 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 12 2/3, Mission Viejo 8 2/3 -- Eli Engle and Dan Roditi swept in 
doubles, 6-0, 7-5, 6-2, for host San Clemente (7-1, 1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 17, Los Amigos 4 -- Thinh Tran swept in singles, 6-3, 6-3, 6-1, for 
host La Quinta (8-1, 4-0). 
</P>
</TEXT>
