<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; CONTRACTS OKD FOR 2 SCHOOL OFFICIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brea Olinda Unified School District trustees have approved two-year contracts 
for the district's two assistant superintendents. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter J. Boothroyd, assistant superintendent of human services, and Gary D. 
Goff, assistant superintendent of business services, have agreed to continue 
working for the district for an annual salary of $81,794 each until June 30, 
1996. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members approved the contracts on a 4-2 vote last week. Trustees Todd A. 
Spitzer and Leonard MacKain cast the dissenting votes. 
</P>
<P>
 Spitzer said he has nothing against the assistant superintendents but feels 
that one-year contracts are more flexible. "I just don't believe in rolling 
over contracts unnecessarily," he said. MacKain agreed. 
</P>
<P>
 Supt. Edgar Z. Seal said that Goff's and Boothroyd's contracts have been 
renewed every two years for the past 12 years.MIMI KO 
</P>
