<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; JAPAN TROUPE TO DO SHOW IN SISTER CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY LOU PICKEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Japanese ballet troupe will perform with its sister city's dancers tonight 
as part of the year's first cultural exchange between Fullerton and Fukui, 
Japan. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-seven ballet students, ranging in age from 7 to 27, arrived in 
Fullerton on Monday evening and are busy touring the city and Disneyland as 
part of their introduction to the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 The dancers will perform three originally choreographed ballet interpretations 
of life in Japan and will wear traditional kimonos while performing classical 
dances. Students from the Nouveau Chamber Ballet of Fullerton will also 
perform. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizer Jerry Conrey said the recital is the culmination of a year's worth 
of planning and is intended to foster friendship between Fullerton and Fukui, 
which became sister cities in1989. 
</P>
<P>
 The recital begins at 7:30 p.m. at the Fullerton College Campus Theatre on the 
corner of Chapman Avenue and Lemon Street. Tickets are $10.50 and $12.50. Call 
(714) 871-8101 for ticket information. MARY LOU PICKEL 
</P>
