ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; TOPLESS BAR GETS ORDER NOT TO OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Orange County Superior Court judge granted a preliminary injunction Tuesday 
that prevents an adult theater and topless dance bar from opening. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach officials requested the injunction last month after concluding 
that the owner of Mermaids might open the business even after the City Council 
rejected his application. 
</P>
<P>
 Judge Warren Siegal is set to decide in a few weeks whether to make his order 
permanent, said Robin Flory, assistant city attorney for Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The owner sought to open Mermaids at a site on Martingale Way near John Wayne 
Airport. But both the Planning Commission and City Council rejected his 
proposal. 
</P>
<P>
 Supporters of the business argued that exotic dancing is a form of free speech 
and that the city did not have the right to deny the permit. 
</P>
<P>
 The city claimed that the business is not permitted under zoning regulations. 
SHELBY GRAD 
