MAN SLAIN IN HALL OF SANTA ANA BOARDINGHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An unidentified man was shot to death in the hallway of a boardinghouse 
Tuesday afternoon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, believed to be between 20 and 30 years old, was shot several times 
in the head and was dead when police arrived at the home in the 1400 block of 
West Cubbon Street at 1:06 p.m., police Cpl.Jeff Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The female owner of the house told investigators that she was in the kitchen 
at the time of the shooting and did not see the suspects or hear conversation 
of any type," Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman told investigators that the victim did not live in the house and 
that she did not know who he was or why he was there, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "She did acknowledge to investigators that she rents several rooms inside of 
the house and the garage to people who then sub-rent their part of the house to 
others," Armstrong said. 
</P>
<P>
 Immediately after the shooting, witnesses told police, they saw two men 
running from the house. They ran east on West Cubbon Street then south on 
Graham Lane toward McFadden Avenue, Armstrong said. 
</P>
