<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GM to Take Charge Against 1994 Earnings: General Motors Corp. announced it 
will take a $758-million hit against 1994 earnings to adopt a new accounting 
standard.GM officials say that despite the heavy onetime financial blow, they 
plan to be profitable this year. The No. 1 U.S. auto maker posted $2.5 billion 
in 1993 profits after years of staggering losses. The $758-million charge, or 
$1.05 per share, will be taken in the first quarter of 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
