America.BMG is one of several big players from the traditional entertainment 
arena that have announced plans to get into the distribution end of the rapidly 
expanding multimedia industry in recent weeks. Crystal is a Silicon Valley 
start-up run by former 20th Century Fox president Strauss Zelnick. Zelnick, who 
does consulting for BMG, denied the persistent rumors that he is planning to 
take an executive position at the media conglomerate. 
