<P>
 Air Fare Sale Spreads Across Continental United States: Led by Trans World 
Airlines, the country's biggest carriers spread an air fare sale to more of the 
country, three days before the offer expires. The sale was started by USAir 
last week and offers round-trip fares of $198, $298 and $398.The cheapest fares 
apply to flights between Eastern cities and Florida, the $298 fares are for 
trips between the East and Midwest and the most expensive tickets are for 
transcontinental trips. United Airlines said it has applied the discounts to 
virtually its entire system in the continental United States, while Delta said 
it has adopted the sale in most markets. American Airlines said it will match 
TWA's expansion in markets where it competes with the St. Louis-based airline. 
