<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK / GIRLS: MELANIE RICHARDSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Camarillo 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Softball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Richardson, a 5-foot-5 right-hander, is 8-1 and has 56 
strikeouts in 57 innings. In her only defeat, she pitched a one-hitter.She has 
given up seven walks and four earned runs, and sports a 0.49 earned-run 
average. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Richardson might never escape the shadow of her older sister 
Laura, who pitched Camarillo to a Southern Section title in 1991 and earned a 
scholarship last season to play for Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. But the younger 
Richardson last week matched her sister's greatest feat of 1993: a victory 
against Simi Valley. Last season, Camarillo -- behind Laura's two-hit, 
11-strikeout performance -- was the only team to beat Simi Valley, which 
finished 26-1-1 and won the Southern Section Division I title. A year later, 
Camarillo has given Simi Valley (8-1), the state's top-ranked team according to 
Cal-Hi Sports, its first loss. Richardson pitched a one-hitter with eight 
strikeouts and beat Sara Griffin (two-hitter, nine strikeouts), the 1993 state 
player of the year. "It was the best game intensity-wise that she has pitched 
for me," Camarillo Coach Darwin Tolzin said. "It kind of reminded me of her 
sister. Her concentration level was very high." 
</P>
