<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / DAILY REPORT; WOMEN'S FINAL FOUR; AT LEAST THESE TAR HEELS 
ARE ALIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Basketball is still being played on the North Carolina campus this week, but 
it's the women's team and not Dean Smith's club that is close to a 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tar Heels (31-2) are making their first appearance in the women's Final 
Four against Purdue on Saturday. The men's team was upset by Boston College in 
the second round of the NCAA tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 "The guys had their chance and they blew it, and we are still in it and we're 
not giving up this chance," said Tonya Sampson, the program's all-time leading 
scorer with 2,106 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
