<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARVARD IS TEAM TO BEAT AT IRVINE TENNIS MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several of the top men's tennis teams in the nation will compete today through 
Saturday in the 15th UC Irvine-Marriott Classic at sites throughout Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 Sixteen schools, including host Irvine, top-seeded Harvard (No. 14 in the 
nation), No. 20 Alabama Birmingham and No. 34 Fresno State, will participate. 
The final is scheduled for 1 p.m. Saturday at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament will be played at UCI Tennis Stadium, Newport Beach Marriott, 
Newport Beach Tennis Club, Balboa Bay Club and Park Newport. 
</P>
