<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK: KELSI ARMBRUSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast, Fr. 
</P>
<P>
 Softball / Pitcher 
</P>
<P>
 Armbruster, from Katella High, is establishing herself as one of the top 
pitchers in the Orange Empire Conference.Armbruster, who throws a paralyzing 
changeup, threw two one-hitters last week for second-place Orange Coast, which 
trails Fullerton by 1 1/2 games. She beat Cypress, 2-1, Monday, then came back 
to beat Riverside, 1-0, Wednesday. Armbruster took Friday off from pitching, 
but contributed with a three-run double as the Pirates beat Irvine Valley, 5-1. 
She has allowed one run and four hits in her last 25 innings. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Kristine Palle, Saddleback, won the 100, 200 and 500 freestyles as the 
Gauchos beat Palomar, 155-142. 
</P>
