<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE ACQUIRE TAPE OF SCENE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As mourners eulogized two college students who were shot to death in a weekend 
carjacking, Los Angeles police confiscated a videotape taken by a bank 
surveillance camera during the crime. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer Sandra Castello said homicide detectives plan to study the tape for 
possible clues to the identity of the gunman who killed Takuma Ito and Go 
Matsuura, both 19, in a San Pedro parking lot Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The tape was recorded by a Bank of San Pedro security camera at an automatic 
teller machine that faces out across the parking lot to the scene of the crime, 
the officer said. 
</P>
<P>
 She said the camera was scanning the area -- a Ralphs supermarket parking lot 
-- from about 80 yards away at the time of the slayings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
