<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFICARE GETS OK TO JOIN STATE HEALTH INSURANCE ALLIANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PacifiCare of California, a subsidiary of PacifiCare Health Systems Inc., said 
Tuesday that it has received approval to participate in the Health Insurance 
Plan of California, the state's alliance through which small businesses can 
purchase health-care coverage. 
</P>
<P>
 Introduced in July, 1993, the state insurance plan covers 2,500 businesses and 
44,000 Californians. The program offers coverage to small employee groups of 
five to 50 employees through a pool of health-care and insurance companies. 
PacifiCare will be one of 23 such members in the state plan. 
</P>
<P>
 Based in Cypress, PacifiCare is one of the largest managed-care organizations 
in the state, serving more than 830,000 customers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA033094-0228 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 027627 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
