<HEADLINE>
<P>
LG&E POWER TO TRANSFER SOME WORKERS, FUNCTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Bloomberg News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LG&E Energy Corp.'s LG&E Power unit said it plans to relocate several 
functions from its Irvine headquarters to Louisville, Ky., as part of a 
restructuring plan announced last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it will relocate an unspecified number of employees from 
Irvine and will fill about 30 managerial and seven clerical and administrative 
staff positions through local hiring and a national recruitment effort over the 
next few months. 
</P>
<P>
 Kathy Campbell, a spokeswoman at LG&E Power, said there were no job cuts 
involved in the relocation. 
</P>
<P>
 The move to Louisville is designed to maximize planning and marketing efforts 
in the growing segment of wholesale power development and marketing, Ed Casey, 
group president of LG&E Energy Services, said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
 LG&E Power's engineering, construction and plant operations staff will remain 
headquartered in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 In November, LG&E Energy Corp. consolidated its various businesses into LG&E 
Energy Services, which will oversee all wholesale power products, development 
and marketing, and Louisville Gas and Electric Co., which will focus on retail 
utility services in the state. 
</P>
<P>
 The supplier of electricity and gas made the consolidations in anticipation of 
intense competition in the closely regulated utility industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
