<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPLICATIONS ACCEPTED FOR WRITERS FILM PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applications are now being accepted for the fifth annual Writer's Film 
Project, a yearlong program sponsored by Amblin Entertainment and Universal 
Pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 The project offers fiction, theater and film writers an opportunity to begin a 
career in screenwriting. The writers are chosen by national competition, which 
last year attracted more than 3,400 applicants. 
</P>
<P>
 Up to 10 writers are chosen to participate, and each receives a $20,000 
stipend. 
</P>
<P>
 Deadline is April 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Call Chesterfield Film at (818) 777-0998. 
</P>
