<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; 10 NAMED TO DESIGN AND PLANNING PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After screening dozens of applications and spending hours interviewing, the 
Ventura City Council has appointed 10 residents to the city's Planning 
Commission and Design Review Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents will serve one- to three-year terms on the advisory panels.The 
seven-member Planning Commission oversees land-use approvals, future planning, 
commercial and residential development proposals and some design review. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-member Design Review Committee makes recommendations to the Planning 
Commission about the design of a proposed project. Decisions by either panel 
can be appealed to the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Ingrid Elsel, Mike Jones, Sandy Smith, Ted Temple and Chuck Thomas were 
appointed Monday night to the Planning Commission. Bob Blossom, Dayle Henry, 
and Nick Deitch were appointed to the Design Review Committee. Curt Stiles and 
Al Okuma were named to both panels. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants were screened by the council's Appointment Recommendation 
Committee, which first reviewed written applications and then conducted oral 
interviews. Council members Gregory L. Carson, Rosa Lee Measures and Jim 
Monahan made the recommendations to the full council Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Next week, the council is expected to appoint 14 residents to the Community 
Affairs Commission, Arts and Cultural Affairs Committee, Tourism and Special 
Events Committee and Historical Preservation Committee. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
